Assessment Objective: Determine if a system and information integrity policy is developed, documented and disseminated to [organization-defined personnel or roles]

Determine if system and information integrity procedures to facilitate the implementation of the system and information integrity policy and associated system and information integrity controls are developed, documented and disseminated to [organization-defined personnel or roles]

Determine if the [organization-defined level] system and information integrity policy addresses purpose, scope, roles, responsibilities, management commitment, coordination among organizational entities, and compliance
Determine if the system and information integrity policy is consistent with applicable laws, Executive Orders, directives, regulations, policies, standards, and guidelines
Determine if the [organization-defined official] is designated to manage the development, documentation, and dissemination of the system and information integrity policy and procedures
Determine if the current system and information integrity policy is reviewed and updated [in accordance with the organization-defined frequency] and after [organization-defined events]
Determine if the current system and information integrity procedures are reviewed and updated [in accordance with the organization-defined frequency] and after [organization-defined events]
Determine if system flaws are identified, reported and corrected
Determine if software and firmware updates related to flaw remediation are tested for effectiveness and potential side effects before installation
Determine if security-relevant software and firmware updates are installed within [organization-defined time period] of the release of the updates
Assessment Parameter: within thirty (30) days of release of updates

Assessment Objective: Determine if flaw remediation is incorporated into the organizational configuration management process
Determine if system components have applicable security-relevant software and firmware updates installed [organization-defined frequency] using [organization-defined automated mechanisms]

Control Name: Time to Remediate Flaws and Benchmarks for Corrective Actions
Assessment Objective: Determine if the time between flaw identification and flaw remediation is measured
Determine if [organization-defined benchmarks] for taking corrective actions have been established
Determine if [signature based; non-signature-based] malicious code protection mechanisms are implemented at system entry and exit points to detect and eradicate malicious code
Determine if malicious code protection mechanisms are updated automatically as new releases are available in accordance with organizational configuration management policy and procedures
Determine if malicious code protection mechanisms are configured to perform periodic scans of the system [organization-defined frequency]

Determine if malicious code protection mechanisms are configured to perform real-time scans of files from external sources at [organization-defined endpoint; network entry and exit points] as the files are downloaded, opened, or executed in accordance with organizational policy
Assessment Parameter: to include endpoints and network entry and exit points

Assessment Objective: Determine if malicious code protection mechanisms are configured to [Selection: block malicious code; quarantine malicious code; take action to be taken in response to malicious code detection] in response to malicious code detection
Assessment Parameter: to include blocking and quarantining malicious code and alerting administrators or defined security personnel near-real-time

Assessment Objective: Determine if malicious code protection mechanisms are configured to send alerts to [organization-defined personnel or roles] in response to malicious code detection
Determine if the receipt of false positives during malicious code detection and eradication and the resulting potential impact on the availability of the system are addressed
Determine if the system is monitored to detect attacks and indicators of potential attacks in accordance with [organization-defined monitoring objectives]
Additional FedRAMP Requirements / Guidan: Guidance: See US-CERT Incident Response Reporting Guidelines

Assessment Objective: Determine if the system is monitored to detect unauthorized local, network and remote connections
Determine if unauthorized use of the system is identified through [organization-defined techniques and methods]
Additional FedRAMP Requirements / Guidan: Guidance: See US-CERT Incident Response Reporting Guidelines

Assessment Objective: Determine if internal monitoring capabilities are invoked or monitoring devices are deployed strategically within the system to collect organization-determined essential information

Determine if internal monitoring capabilities are invoked or monitoring devices are deployed at ad hoc locations within the system to track specific types of transactions of interest to the organization
Determine if detected events and anomalies are analyzed
Determine if the level of system monitoring activity is adjusted when there is a change in risk to organizational operations and assets, individuals, other organizations, or the Nation
Determine if a legal opinion regarding system monitoring activities is obtained

Additional FedRAMP Requirements / Guidan: Guidance: See US-CERT Incident Response Reporting Guidelines

Assessment Objective: Determine if individual intrusion detection tools are connected and configured to a system-wide intrusion detection system;

Control Name: Automated Tools and Mechanisms for Real-time Analysis
Assessment Objective: Determine if automated tools and mechanisms are employed to support a near real-time analysis of events
Determine if criteria for unusual or unauthorized activities or conditions for inbound and outbound communications traffic are defined
Determine if inbound and outbound communications traffic is monitored [organization-defined frequency] for [organization-defined unusual or unauthorized activities or conditions]
Assessment Parameter: continuously; CSP-defined unusual or unauthorized activities or conditions

Assessment Objective: Determine if [organization-defined personnel or roles] are alerted when system-generated [organization-defined compromise indicators] occur
Assessment Parameter: CSP-defined personnel or roles; CSP-defined compromise indicators
Additional FedRAMP Requirements / Guidan: Guidance: In accordance with the incident response plan

Assessment Objective: Determine if provisions are made so that [organization-defined encrypted communications traffic] is visible to [organization-defined system monitoring tools and mechanisms]
Additional FedRAMP Requirements / Guidan: Requirement: The service provider must support Agency requirements to comply with M-21-31 (https://www.whitehouse.gov/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/M-21-31-Improving-the-Federal-Governments-Investigative-and-Remediation-Capabilities-Related-to-Cybersecurity-Incidents.pdf) and M-22-09 (https://www.whitehouse.gov/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/M-22-09.pdf).

Assessment Objective: Determine if outbound communications traffic at the external interfaces and [organization-defined interior points] to the system is analyzed to discover anomalies

Determine if [organization-defined personnel or roles] is/are alerted using [organization-defined automated mechanisms] when [organization-defined activities that trigger alerts] indicate inappropriate or unusual activities with security or privacy implications
Assessment Parameter: CSP-defined personnel or roles; CSP-defined automated mechanisms; CSP-defined activities that trigger alerts

Assessment Objective: Determine if a wireless intrusion detection system is employed to identify rogue wireless devices, detect attack attempts and detect potential compromises or breaches to the system
Determine if information from monitoring tools and mechanisms employed throughout the system is correlated
Determine if outbound communications traffic is analyzed at interfaces external to the system and [organization-defined interior points] to detect covert exfiltration of information
Determine if [organization-defined additional monitoring] is implemented on individuals who have been identified by [organization-defined sources] as posing an increased level of risk
Determine if [organization-defined additional monitoring] of privileged users is implemented
Determine if network services that have not been authorized or approved by [organization-defined authorization or approval processes] are detected

Determine if [organization-defined audit; alert
organization-defined personnel or roles] is/are initiated when network services that have not been authorized or approved by authorization or approval processes are detected
Assessment Parameter: CSP-defined audit or alert of CSP-defined personnel or roles

Assessment Objective: Determine if [organization-defined host-based monitoring mechanisms] are implemented on [organization-defined system components]
Assessment Parameter: CSP-defined host-based monitoring mechanisms; CSP-defined system components

Assessment Objective: Determine if system security alerts, advisories, and directives are received from [organization-defined external organizations] on an ongoing basis
Assessment Parameter: to include US-CERT and Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA) Directives
Additional FedRAMP Requirements / Guidan: Requirement: Service Providers must address the CISA Emergency and Binding Operational Directives applicable to their cloud service offering per FedRAMP guidance.  This includes listing the applicable directives and stating compliance status

Assessment Objective: Determine if internal security alerts, advisories, and directives are generated as deemed necessary

Determine if security alerts, advisories, and directives are disseminated to [organization-defined [organization-defined personnel or roles]; [organization-defined elements]; [organization-defined external organizations]
Assessment Parameter: to include system security personnel and administrators with configuration/patch-management responsibilities

Assessment Objective: Determine if security directives are implemented in accordance with established time frames or if the issuing organization is notified of the degree of noncompliance
Determine if [organization-defined automated mechanisms] are used to broadcast security alert and advisory information throughout the organization
Determine if [organization-defined security and privacy functions] are verified to be operating correctly

Determine if [organization-defined security and privacy functions] are verified [organization-defined system transitional states]; upon command by user with appropriate privilege; [organization-defined frequency]
Assessment Parameter: to include upon system startup and/or restart; at least monthly

Assessment Objective: Determine if [organization-defined personnel or roles] is/are alerted to failed security and privacy verification tests
Assessment Parameter: to include system administrators and security personnel

Assessment Objective:
Determine if [organization-defined shut the
system down; restart the system; [organization-defined alternative action(s)] is/are initiated when anomalies are discovered
Assessment Parameter: CSP-defined shut down or restart the system; CSP-defined alternative action

Assessment Objective: Determine if integrity verification tools are employed to detect unauthorized changes to [organization-defined software, firmware and information]
Determine if [organization-defined actions] are taken when unauthorized changes to the software, firmware and information, are detected

Determine if an integrity check of [organization-defined software, firmware and information] is performed [Selection: at startup; at [organization-defined transitional states or security-relevant events]; [organization-defined frequency]]
Assessment Parameter: CSP-defined software, firmware, and information; selection to include security relevant events; at least monthly

Assessment Objective: Determine if automated tools that provide notification to [organization-defined personnel or roles] upon discovering discrepancies during integrity verification are employed
Assessment Parameter: to include the ISSO and/or similar roles within the organization

Assessment Objective:
Determine if [organization-defined shut down the
system; restart the system; implement organization-defined controls] are automatically performed when integrity violations are discovered
Assessment Parameter: CSP-defined selection: shut down the system; restart the system; implement CSP-defined controls

Assessment Objective: Determine if the detection of [organization-defined security-relevant changes to the system] are incorporated into the organizational incident response capability
Determine if cryptographic mechanisms are implemented to authenticate [organization-defined software or firmware components] prior to installation
Assessment Parameter: to include all software and firmware inside the boundary

Assessment Objective: Determine if spam protection mechanisms are employed at system entry and exit points to detect and act on unsolicited messages
Additional FedRAMP Requirements / Guidan:
Guidance: When CSO sends email on behalf of the government as part of the business offering, Control Description should include implementation of Domain-based Message Authentication, Reporting & Conformance (DMARC) on the sending domain for outgoing messages as described in DHS Binding Operational Directive (BOD) 18-01.
https://cyber.dhs.gov/bod/18-01/ 

Guidance: CSPs should confirm DMARC configuration (where appropriate) to ensure that policy=reject and the parameter includes reports@dmarc.cyber.dhs.gov.  DMARC compliance should be documented in the SI-08 control implementation solution description, and list the FROM: domain(s) that will be seen by email recipients.

Assessment Objective: Determine if spam protection mechanisms are updated when new releases are available in accordance with organizational configuration management policies and procedures
Determine if spam protection mechanisms are automatically updated [organization-defined frequency]
Determine if the validity of the [organization-defined information inputs] is checked
Additional FedRAMP Requirements / Guidan: Requirement: Validate all information inputs and document any exceptions

Assessment Objective: Determine if error messages that provide the information necessary for corrective actions are generated without revealing information that could be exploited
Determine if error messages are revealed only to [organization-defined personnel or roles]
Assessment Parameter: to include the ISSO and/or similar role within the organization

Assessment Objective: Determine if information within the system and information output from the system is managed and retained in accordance with applicable laws, Executive Orders, directives, regulations, policies, standards, guidelines, and operational requirements
Determine if [organization-defined controls] are implemented to protect the system memory from unauthorized code execution
